  <title>Question 8</title>
  <p>
    A ship leaves the port of San Diego and is moving at a constant speed. 
    After traveling 2 miles, the ship has a bearing of <m> N57&#176;W </m>. 
    If the ship turns <m> 90&#176; </m> and heads towards the southwest, approximate 
    how many more miles the ship needs to travel until it has a bearing of 
    <m> S71&#176;W </m>? Round your answer to the nearest whole mile. Draw a 
    picture to illustrate this word problem.
  </p>
  <solution>
    <p>
      <image source = "Q8_pic.png" width = "75%" />
      About <m> 3 </m> miles.
    </p>
  </solution>
</section>